00:42.500 --> 00:50.620
This is Bill Vernon and Daryl Lane. How many science fiction works feature
spacecraft capable of planet hopping, interstellar travel, or even galaxy

00:50.620 --> 00:57.820
galloping? Yet in our experience, we know it takes several days' travel to reach
even the moon, and years to reach the nearest planets. Travel to the stars is

00:57.820 --> 01:05.480
presently unthinkable. In space opera, the writer usually invokes some kind of
faster-than-light drive, which glosses over the basics of the special theory of

01:05.480 --> 01:13.060
relativity. We asked physicist and science fiction writer Robert Forward how it
may be possible to travel faster than light. When you talk about going faster

01:13.060 --> 01:24.580
than light, really what you want to do is get from here to there, without
traveling all the steps in between. If you can do that, then you can go faster

01:24.580 --> 01:34.880
than light. There's two ways, at least, that I know to do that. One is to find a
space warp. You jump into the space warp, you go into a hyperspace, and then you

01:34.880 --> 01:46.180
come out of another space warp somewhere else in our universe. And if you can do
that in a time shorter than it takes you to travel over the top line, then

01:46.180 --> 01:54.840
you've done that. An amazing thing about it is the Einstein general theory of
relativity has space warps in it. Going through a space warp is one way to get

01:54.840 --> 02:06.800
around the speed of light limit. And what's the second way? Then the other way
to go faster than the speed of light is to destroy the space between you and

02:06.800 --> 02:21.460
where you want to go. Now this space drive theory was invented by a student of
Roger Penrose. He's a scientific expert and relativist that works with Hawking

02:21.460 --> 02:34.260
on gravitation. He's working on a thing called twister theory. And in the
twister theory, the real universe is not what we see. That's only a reduced

02:34.260 --> 02:44.620
image of it. The real universe is an eight-dimensional universe that's made up
of twisters. And the twisters not only make up all the particles in the space

02:44.620 --> 02:55.380
and time that we live in, it even makes up the space and the time. It takes a
certain collection of twisters to make up a point in space. It takes another

02:55.380 --> 03:07.300
collection of twisters to make up a point in time. This collection of twisters
is a fairly uniform thing, and that's why we see space as it is, according to

03:07.300 --> 03:17.660
Penrose. Now we don't know whether the twister theory is correct, but Roger is
hoping that it will turn out to be an accurate method, I mean, accurate theory

03:17.660 --> 03:28.380
for the universe. So how does one build a faster-than-light drive based on the
twister theory of Penrose and his students? If you warp the twister space too

03:28.380 --> 03:40.300
much, give it a real strong warp, then it's no longer ordered well enough to
make a piece of space or a piece of time. So if you take a piece of twister

03:40.300 --> 03:51.480
space and you warp it badly, the space and the time that it used to make now
disappears. It's no longer there. So their version of a different kind of a

03:51.480 --> 04:02.540
faster-than-light drive is you take a spacecraft up, you get it out in the way
from the planets and so forth, and then you turn on the twister warping machine

04:02.540 --> 04:16.900
in your spacecraft on the side towards Alpha Centauri, and you just warp that
space so much that you warp that twister space so much that the space-time

04:16.900 --> 04:25.220
between here and Alpha Centauri disappears. And what you'll see if you're
sitting in a spacecraft is that all of a sudden Alpha Centauri just come right

04:25.220 --> 04:35.160
towards you, and then pretty soon you look out one window, you see the sun, you
look out the other window, you'll see Alpha Centauri. Then the machine inside

04:35.160 --> 04:44.420
the spacecraft unwarps the space, but on the other side of the spacecraft, and
all that space now reappears between the spacecraft and the sun. You watch the

04:44.420 --> 04:51.320
sun recede off into the distance while you stay there with Alpha Centauri. So
that's another way to get there. You just get rid of the space between here and

04:51.320 --> 04:51.500
there.

