12:00.880 --> 12:02.600
And here are your hosts.

12:06.700 --> 12:14.740
This is David Carson. And Daryl Lane. We're talking with Teresa Patterson,
Science Fiction fan and award-winning costume designer. Patterson believes that

12:14.740 --> 12:21.100
the best costumes are those that make the science fiction or fantasy character
come to life for the viewers. Therefore, in addition to constructing the costume

12:21.100 --> 12:28.980
itself, she also creates a setting and sort of a brief script to put the
character in. She takes us through one of her creations. Now, I also have

12:28.980 --> 12:37.940
another one that has been extremely successful. It's called Morgan Le Fay. And
the character, basically, I was sitting around trying to think of what is a

12:37.940 --> 12:47.340
really way-out character that's not all that well-known, but that could command
the stage and make that same kind of reality come about. And it occurred to me

12:47.340 --> 12:55.460
that very little has been done with the sorceress, Morgan Le Fay, who's from the
Arthurian legend and who was the one that eventually defeated Merlin. And I

12:55.460 --> 13:05.260
thought, if I can make this character do a spell on stage so that the audience
really believes it, that that would be an excellent kind of costume to do. So I

13:05.260 --> 13:13.000
designed the costume. And of course, it's different than designing a costume for
a movie character or a television character because it was completely up to my

13:13.000 --> 13:25.740
imagination what I wanted to do with it. So I used a lot of reds and blacks and
lots of gold and to create a total effect of color but somber evil color and

13:25.740 --> 13:36.840
made a very large headdress with lots of sparkles on it to catch the light and
designed it in such a way so that it would give the impression of an evil

13:36.840 --> 13:45.520
sorceress who had a lot of power and was a ruler in her own right and designed
the cloak so that it would actually fold out into a half circle so that it would

13:45.520 --> 13:53.400
look like bat wings on the back. The costume was beautiful, but that's not
enough. What Patterson had to come up with was something for Morgan Le Fay to

13:53.400 --> 14:00.900
do. Then she had to locate a soundtrack that would somehow convey the evil and
menace of the sorceress. Patterson did both of these things. Then she added a

14:00.900 --> 14:10.120
little extra to the sound effects. And then I added a soundtrack record which
had thunder and lightning on it and went into my handy-dandy little stereo set

14:10.120 --> 14:17.040
in the middle of the living room, bought a bunch of patch cords from Radio Shack
so that the room looked like Spaghetti'sville and patched it all together and

14:17.040 --> 14:26.640
using a normal hand mic and a reverb effect from the speakers being on at the
same time as the recording managed to get an evil reverberating sound to the

14:26.640 --> 14:35.560
voice, lightning and thunder in the background, this awesome evil music building
and flowing and a high climax and then fading out in the distance. So I had a

14:35.560 --> 14:40.000
wonderful soundtrack and if the mic failed, I'd still be fine because I had it
all on tape.

14:48.280 --> 14:56.480
Finally, she describes the presentation of the character at a convention before
a large audience. And the way the actual skit came off was something like this.

14:56.700 --> 15:08.340
The stage would darken and then you'd see a red glow moving up onto the stage
and you'd see just the outline of this bizarre golden mask and a red-garbed

15:08.340 --> 15:17.220
woman holding the red globe. And the music starts and starts to build and all of
a sudden the spell starts and then suddenly there's a burst of flame from the

15:17.220 --> 15:24.780
red globe. And as the spell builds and she starts summoning the darkness, the
room gets darker for a moment and then there's another burst of flame and the

15:24.780 --> 15:33.540
room starts to lighten just a little bit and the spell builds and builds until
finally she banishes the light from her and says darkness be gone and then

15:33.540 --> 15:42.760
blasts this huge shot of fire blue flame straight up into the sky and the
darkness is gone. And then she tells you that she is Morgan Le Fay and then

15:42.760 --> 15:52.720
demonstrates the costume and shows the wide wings of the bat and slowly walks
off as the thunder fades into the distance. Again, I got a standing ovation. The

15:52.720 --> 16:04.480
costume has never not won a prize. It has always been first and second
everywhere I've taken it. And there are better costumes but it comes to life and

16:04.480 --> 16:12.100
that's what the people are looking for is a way to bring their fantasies and
their dreams into reality so they can touch them so it's something they can

16:12.100 --> 16:16.780
really have a tangible experience from. More with Teresa Patterson next time.

